  "abstract": "The ICCV2, and extra-short-duration and fusarium wilt-resistant variety has extended kabuli gram cultivation to central and peninsular India for the first time. Its early growth vigour, flexible time of planting, suitability to rainfed and irrigated conditions and premium price have made kabuli gram and cash crop in these regions.",
